From: Refracta user
Date: 2026-07-15
Subject: [PATCH v4] refractasnapshot: seed /etc/skel + UEFI mode; theme-aware xterm; elapsed time; custom icons

Building on v1 (skel-seed + UEFI mode), v2 (theme-aware xterm), v3 (elapsed
time). This v4 is cosmetic-only: custom window/dialog/launcher icons so the
snapshot GUI stops showing yad's default green-flask logo.

  1. Window icon (titlebar / taskbar / alt-tab): a custom Refracta snapshot icon
     is used for every yad dialog, set in the DIALOG="yad ..." definition and on
     the standalone "Snapshot Help" dialog.
  2. Final dialog image: final_message()'s "All finished!" dialog now shows the
     custom icon as its in-dialog image (was gtk-dialog-info).
  3. Launcher icon: usr/share/applications/refractasnapshot.desktop now points at
     the custom icon (was Icon=system, a blank page).

The icon is a new SVG installed to
usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/refractasnapshot.svg, referenced by
absolute path so it renders regardless of icon theme/cache.

What changes (v4):
  - refractasnapshot-gui: define REFRACTA_ICON; set the window icon in the
    DIALOG definition + the Help dialog; use the custom icon as final_message()'s
    --image.
  - usr/share/applications/refractasnapshot.desktop: Icon=.
  - NEW usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/refractasnapshot.svg.
  - refractasnapshot-wrapper.sh, refractasnapshot (CLI) and skel-seed-lib.sh:
    unchanged from v3.

